RIYADH: The 8th Kings and Princes Cups Festival concluded on Saturday at King Abdulaziz Racetrack in Janadriyah. For the latest updates, follow us on Twitter @ArabNewsSport The horse racing event, organized by the Jockey Club of Saudi Arabia in honor the Kingdomâ€™s former kings and princes, included five main rounds of racing over a range of distances in a number of categories, which are named after King Saud bin Abdulaziz, King Faisal bin Abdulaziz, King Khalid bin Abdulaziz and King Fahd bin Abdulaziz. Each round carried prize money of SR800,000 ($213,000). The second edition of the Imam Turki bin Abdullah Sword round also took place on Saturday, which had a prize of SR900,000.